==English==
===Etymology===
From the Norse [[Vanir]].
===Proper Noun===
'''Vanir'''
#the principal deities, as a group, of the Norse pantheon that represent chaos, fertility, and cultivation; opponents of the [[Æsir]].

==Norse==
===Etymology===
From the Proto-Indo-European root ''*wen-'', ''to strive''.
===Proper Noun===
'''Vanir'''
#the principal deities, as a group, of the Norse pantheon that represent chaos, fertility, and cultivation; opponents of the [[Æsir]].

